\par }{\b\f1\fs18\cf17\insrsid5405 Installing UAF}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 
\par 
\par The first step of installation is to download the latest build. See }{\f1\fs18\uldb\insrsid5405 here}{\v\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 !KLink(Contact)}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  for details.
\par 
\par Double-click the downloaded file and Dungeon Craft will install itself. After the installation is completed there will be several folders created under the root Dungeon Craft install folder.
\par 
\par UAF             - root install folder
\par UAF/DefaultArt  - contains all default art and sound files used by editor
\par UAF/GPDL        - GPDL script engine executables
\par UAF/help        - source for the help file
\par UAF/UAFWin      - contains UAFWin.exe, the engine used to play a saved design
\par UAF/UAFWinEd    - contains UAFWinEd.exe, the editor used to create a design
\par UAF/src         - contains all source code
\par UAF/BACKUP      - backup of files updated during most recent install
\par 
\par Dungeon Craft is composed of two executables. UAFWinEd.exe is the editor, and UAFWin.exe is the game engine. The editor creates a stand-alone design that includes all art, sounds, config files. The GPDL script engine is a separate executable tha
t is used from a command line.
