\par }{\b\f1\fs18\cf17\insrsid5405 Config File}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 
\par 
\par When the editor first starts it looks for a configuration file.  Usually this is a file named "config.txt" that is in the root install directory.  But the editor will load the config.txt file that is with a design when loading a design.
\par 
\par You may also speci
fy the name of the configuration file on the UAFWinEd command line.  This is useful if, for example, you want the editor to reside in a "binary programs" directory and then be referenced by shortcuts in one or more UAF directories.  If a filename is speci
fied on the command line it must reside in the "working" directory.  In the case of shortcuts, this can be specified as one of the shortcut's properties.
\par 
\par The interesting parts of the config file are:
\par 
\par }{\f5\fs18\insrsid5405 
\par // Root directory containing UAF installation.
\par Install_Dir  = I:\\MyUAF
\par 
\par // Path to default art/sound folder
\par Default_Resources = i:\\MyUAF\\DefaultArt
\par 
\par // Path to the game executable that will be copied
\par // to each design folder when design is saved
\par Game_Exec    = i:\\MyUAF\\UAFWin.exe
\par }{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 
\par 
