\par }{\b\f1\fs18\cf17\insrsid5405 UnDo}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 
\par 
\par The operations you perform while editing are recorded in a last-in-first-out queue; a stack. You can cancel, or undo, the last operation by selecting 'UnDo' from the 'Level' menu or by using the Control-Z key on your keyboard.
\par 
\par Several operations are recorded. You can undo multiple operations by successively pressing Control-Z. Once an operation is 'undone' it is forgotten and there is no way to 're-do' it except to do it again.
\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\sb50\sa50\keepn\nowidctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 \page }{\cs18\super\insrsid5405\charrsid5405 ${\footnote\ftnalt \pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 
