\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\b\f1\fs18\cf17\insrsid5405 Global Game Configuration}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 
\par 
\par Global settings are generally those that have effect during the entire game, regardless of which level is currently being played. To begin editing the global settings, use menu option 'Global->Global Settings' or just CTRL-G.
\par 
\par A screen shot of the global settings window is below:
\par \{bmc images\\GlobalSettings.bmp\} 
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Design Name}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  The current name for your design. This name does not need to match the saved folder name you store the design files in.
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Starting Exp}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  This experience is given to all new characters created by created by player.
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Starting Platinum/Gem/Jewelry}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  These funds will be given to all new characters created by the player.
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Starting Location}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  This determines where the player begins a new game. You can select the starting level, the xy coord, and initial party facing. Only levels which have been created an
d saved will be displayed in the starting level list. You can also set the initial game clock time (24 hour format, 0000-2359).
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Time Delta Per Party Step}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  These four settings determine how much game clock time elapses for each party step.
\par }{\f3\fs18\insrsid5405 \'b7}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 \tab  Dungeon - dungeon maps, not searching
\par }{\f3\fs18\insrsid5405 \'b7}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 \tab  Dungeon Search - dungeon maps, search mode enabled
\par }{\f3\fs18\insrsid5405 \'b7}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 \tab  Wilderness - wilderness maps, not searching
\par }{\f3\fs18\insrsid5405 \'b7}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 \tab  Wilderness Search - wilderness maps, search mode enabled
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Min Party Size}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  The minimum number of party members needed before a player is allowed to begin adventuring.
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Max Party Size}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  The maximum number of party members allowed before a player is allowed to begin adventuring.
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Allow Char Create}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  If checked, the player can create new characters. If not checked, the player cannot create new characters and must use whatever pre-generated characters the designer has made available.

\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Various Border/Frame Buttons}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  You can use these buttons to customize the artwork used during game play.
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Font}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  You can choose which Window's font will be used dur
ing game play. You should use a common font. If the specified font is not installed on the computer where your design is played, the closest matching font will be used. The font size can also be chosen. The minimum font size is 8pts, but no maximum is enf
o
rced. The game screens will not adapt to fonts which cannot fit in the allotted space. Text which will not fit will either run on into the next screen area, or be truncated. You should test your design with some long character/item/monster names if you se
lect a large font size.
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Icon Background}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  This image is only used during new character creation, and is the backdrop against which possible combat icons are displayed.
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Title Screen}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  This image is displayed when the game starts. It will continue to be displayed until the player presses a key. If no image is specified, then the starting menu will be the first thing displayed.

\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Screen Background}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  The default background is entirely filled with the color black, and no background image is specified. You can choose a
 background image that will be the background for all non-combat screens. This image is drawn first, and all other art is drawn on top of the background image.
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Starting Equipment}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  This lets you choose which items will be given to all new characters created by the player.
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Sounds}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  To edit the default global sounds played during the game.
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Currency}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  To edit the names and conversion rates of up to 10 currency types. By default, the FRUA money types are used.
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Difficulty Settings}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  To edit the five game difficulty settings. You can change each difficulty level name, as well as what affect it will have on game play.
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Global Attributes}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  This is a means of enabling the behavior of older version
s of Dungeon Craft. This will display the currently available game play options, and the version at which each will behave as. By default, all available options will behave as the most current Dungeon Craft version. You can selectively alter a specific op
tion to behave as if the game were running at an older version if you wish.
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Auto Darken Viewport}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  This is way of simulating nightfall or darkness. If enabled, it will automatically darken the viewport during the specified times. The Auto Darken Amount range
