\par }{\b\f1\fs18\cf17\insrsid5405 Place Walls}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 
\par 
\par Placing a wall means both putting a visible wall on the side of a square and setting the 'blockage' state.  These are two independent attributes of one of the square's sides.
\par 
\par When you }{\f1\fs18\uldb\insrsid5405 select a wall to be placed}{\v\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 !ALink(SelectWall)}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 
 you also make a decision about whether the wall is 'open', 'locked', etc.  It is perfectly reasonable, for example, to have one side of a room blocked without any visible wall.  More common is a wall with a doorway that is 'open' or unblocked.
\par 
\par There are basically two ways of placing walls in your design:
\par 
\par }{\f3\fs18\insrsid5405 \'b7}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 \tab }{\f1\fs18\uldb\insrsid5405 Place walls using 3-d view.}{\v\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 !ALink(PlaceWallsOn3d)}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 
\par }{\f3\fs18\insrsid5405 \'b7}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 \tab }{\f1\fs18\uldb\insrsid5405 Place walls using the 2-d map}{\v\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 !ALink(PlaceWallsOn2d)}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 
\par 
\par You need not decide on one method and use it exclusively.  Both methods are active and can be used at the same time.
\par 
\par If you make a mistake (or even mistakes) when placing a wall there are three methods of correcting your mistake:
\par 
\par }{\f3\fs18\insrsid5405 \'b7}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 \tab }{\f1\fs18\uldb\insrsid5405 Delete the wall}{\v\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 !ALink(DeleteWall)}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  just placed.
\par }{\f3\fs18\insrsid5405 \'b7}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 \tab Use the editor's '}{\f1\fs18\uldb\insrsid5405 UnDo}{\v\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 !ALink(UnDo)}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 ' capability
\par }{\f3\fs18\insrsid5405 \'b7}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 \tab }{\f1\fs18\uldb\insrsid5405 Replace the wall}{\v\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 !ALink(ReplaceWall)}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  with the correct wall.
\par 
\par Again, all these methods are usable at the same time.  Only habit will decide which is most convenient for you in any situation.
\par 
\par You might be interested in knowing that you can also manipulate the placement of walls and the blockage state of walls at runtime.  See }{\f1\fs18\uldb\insrsid5405 Level Associated String List}{\v\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 !ALink(Level Associated String List)}{
