\par }{\b\f1\fs18\cf17\insrsid5405 Placing Wall using 3-d View}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 
\par 
\par In this method of placing walls, you 'walk' around the design as if you were playing the game and put walls to your left, right, and front.  There are two ways to move around using the 3-d View:
\par 
\par }{\f3\fs18\insrsid5405 \'b7}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 \tab }{\f1\fs18\uldb\insrsid5405 The arrow keys}{\v\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 !ALink(ArrowMove3d)}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 .
\par }{\f3\fs18\insrsid5405 \'b7}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 \tab }{\f1\fs18\uldb\insrsid5405 The mouse}{\v\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 !ALink(MouseMove3d)}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 .
\par 
\par There are several ways of placing a wall in the 3-d view:
\par 
\par }{\f3\fs18\insrsid5405 \'b7}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 \tab Left-click the appropriate button just below the view.
\par }{\f3\fs18\insrsid5405 \'b7}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 \tab Press the appropriate letter on your keyboard.
\par }{\f3\fs18\insrsid5405 \'b7}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 \tab Left-click the space in the 3-d view.
\par 
\par The three buttons below the 3-d view are labeled 'Left', 'Place Wall', and 'Right'.  The first letter of each o
f these commands can be used to place the walls from the keyboard.  The walls are placed in the space you are currently 'occupying', to your left, front, and right, respectively.
\par 
\par If you have '}{\f1\fs18\uldb\insrsid5405 KwikKlik}{\v\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 !KLink(KwikKlik)}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 ' enabled then you can also place walls
 using the mouse in the 3-d view.  The view is divided into 3 equal horizontal stripes and the center stripe is made up of 5 equal squares.  The 5 squares from left to right represent:
\par }{\f3\fs18\insrsid5405 \'b7}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 \tab Left wall of room you are in
\par }{\f3\fs18\insrsid5405 \'b7}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 \tab Left wall of room just ahead
\par }{\f3\fs18\insrsid5405 \'b7}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 \tab Front wall of room you are in
\par }{\f3\fs18\insrsid5405 \'b7}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 \tab Right wall of room just ahead
\par }{\f3\fs18\insrsid5405 \'b7}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 \tab Right wall of room you are in
\par You place a wall by left-clicking the appropriate square and }{\f1\fs18\uldb\insrsid5405 delete a wall}{\v\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 !ALink(DeleteWall)}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  by right-clicking.  All much easier done than said.
\par 
\par No matter what method y
ou use, placing a wall can mean either placing a single wall on one side of one room or it can mean placing two identical walls back-to-back.  The choice is made by 'checking' or 'un-checking' the 'Place Wall on both Sides' option in the 'Mode' menu.

