\par }{\b\f1\fs18\cf17\insrsid5405 Show Access}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 
\par 
\par The 'Level' menu has a 'Show Access' option that can be toggled on or off.  When it is on, the wall-editing mode colors the squares to indicate whether or not they can be reached from the current position with spells, keys, etc.
\par 
\par Each level has its own individual rules for deciding whether a square can be reached from an adjacent square.  The default is generally:
\par 
\par }{\f3\fs18\insrsid5405 \'b7}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 \tab Red - Access marked 'Locked'.
\par 
\par }{\f3\fs18\insrsid5405 \'b7}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 \tab Green - Access marked 'Spell to Open'.
\par 
\par }{\f3\fs18\insrsid5405 \'b7}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 \tab Blue - Access marked 'Locked Key n'.
\par 
\par The colors are additive so that an area that would be both red and green will be colored yellow.
\par 
\par The criteria for each of the three access rules can be modified to suit your particular needs by using the 'Access Options...' item in the 'Level' menu.  Your criteria will be saved with 
the level currently being edited and you can specify different criteria for each level.
