\par }{\b\f1\fs18\cf17\insrsid5405 Logic Block Gates}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 
\par 
\par The seven gates are identical to one another.  Each has an input from the top and an input from the side.  For non-commutative operations the
 top input is the 'left' input and the side input is the 'right' input.  For example, the Arithmetic Minus operation subtracts the side from the top.
\par 
\par If the gate requires a logical value or an integer as an input then it translates the input as described in }{\f1\fs18\uldb\insrsid5405 Logic Block Values}{\v\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 !ALink(LogicBlockValues)}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 
\par 
\par }{\f1\fs18\cf6\insrsid5405 Copy From Top}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 
\par The default.
\par Top input and result are strings.  Side input is ignored.
\par Result = The value from the top input.  Side input ignored
\par 
\par }{\f1\fs18\cf6\insrsid5405 Copy From Side}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 
\par Side input and result are strings.  Top input ignored.
\par Result = The value from the side input.  Top input is ignored.
\par 
\par }{\f1\fs18\cf6\insrsid5405 Logical AND}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 
\par Top and side inputs and result are logical values.
\par Result is true if both top is true and side is true.
\par 
\par }{\f1\fs18\cf6\insrsid5405 Logical OR}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 
\par Top and side inputs and result are logical values.
\par Result is true if either top is true or side is true (or both are true).
\par 
\par }{\f1\fs18\cf6\insrsid5405 Numeric Plus}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 
\par Top and side inputs and result are integers.
\par Result is the ordinary addition you learned in grade school.
\par 
\par }{\f1\fs18\cf6\insrsid5405 Numeric Minus}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 
\par Top and side inputs and result are integers.
\par Result = ordinary subtraction.  Top input minus side input.
\par 
\par }{\f1\fs18\cf6\insrsid5405 Numeric Multiply}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 
\par Top and side inputs are integers.  Result is integer.
\par Ordinary multiplication.
\par 
\par }{\f1\fs18\cf6\insrsid5405 Numeric Divide}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 
\par Top and side and result are integers.
\par Signed division.  Top divided by side.  Mathematicians beware....the result of dividing -5 by 3 is -1.  Any remainder has the same sign as the dividend.
\par You should also know that this division is done on the strings of digits and is therefore quite slow.  Dividing a 60-digit number by a 30-digit number to get a 30-digit quotient requires about 900 microseconds on my lowly Pentium 166.
\par 
\par }{\f1\fs18\cf6\insrsid5405 Numeric Modulo}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 
\par Top and side and result are integers.
\par Result is the remainder when the top is divided by the side.  Again, mathematicians beware....the remainder has the same sign as the dividend.  For example, -8 modulo 3 is -2.
\par Also, see warning about speed in description of Numeric Divide.
\par 
\par }{\f1\fs18\cf6\insrsid5405 Numeric Greater}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 
\par Top and side inputs are integers.  Result is logical true or false.
\par Result is true if top input is greater than side input.
\par 
\par }{\f1\fs18\cf6\insrsid5405 GREP}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 
\par Top input and side inputs are strings.
\par Result is a string.  Result is the substring of the top input matched by the grep expression from the side input.  You might use this to search an item list for a particular item.  Examples:
\par }{\f3\fs18\insrsid5405 \'b7}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 \tab "This is odd" GREP "odd"  =  "odd"
\par }{\f3\fs18\insrsid5405 \'b7}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 \tab "abcdefghijklmnop" GREP "e.*l"  =  "efghijkl"
