\par }{\b\f1\fs18\cf17\insrsid5405 Logic Block Actions}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 
\par 
\par You can perform up to two actions either unconditionally or depending on the result of the computation of Gate-L.
\par 
\par Many of the actions have parameters as described below:
\par 
\par }{\f1\fs18\cf6\insrsid5405 Do Nothing}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 
\par As you expect.  Nothing gets done.
\par 
\par }{\f1\fs18\cf6\insrsid5405 Set Global ASL}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 
\par Define an entry in the global Associated String List (ASL) (See  }{\f1\fs18\uldb\insrsid5405 Associated String Lists}{\v\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 !KLink(Associated String Lists)}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 
).  The parameter provides the key for the entry and its new value separated by an equal sign.  If no equal sign exists, the entire parameter is taken to be the key and the value becomes the empty string.
\par 
\par }{\f1\fs18\cf6\insrsid5405 Set Level ASL}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 
\par Define an entry in the level Associated String List (ASL) (See }{\f1\fs18\uldb\insrsid5405 Associated String Lists}{\v\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 !ALink(Associated String Lists)}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 ).  The paramet
er provides the level number and key for the entry and its new value separated by an equal sign.  If no equal sign exists, the entire parameter is taken to be the key and the value becomes the empty string.  The level is assumed to be the party's current 
level if the level number and the slashes are omitted.
\par 
\par The entire parameter takes the form:
\par /level/key=value
\par 
\par }{\f1\fs18\cf6\insrsid5405 Set Party ASL}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 
\par Define an party's Associated String List (ASL) (See }{\f1\fs18\uldb\insrsid5405 Associated String Lists}{\v\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 !ALink(Associated String Lists)}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 ).  The parameter provides
 the entry's key and its new value separated by an equal sign.  If no equal sign exists, the entire parameter is taken to be the key and the value becomes the empty string.
\par 
\par }{\f1\fs18\cf6\insrsid5405 Set Temporary ASL}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 
\par Define an entry in the temporary Associated String List (ASL) (See }{\f1\fs18\uldb\insrsid5405 Associated String Lists}{\v\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 !ALink(Associated String Lists)}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 
).  The parameter provides the entry's key and its new value separated by an equal sign.  If no equal sign exists, the entire parameter is taken to be the key and the value becomes the empty string.
\par 
\par }{\f1\fs18\cf6\insrsid5405 Remove Global ASL}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 
\par The parameter is taken to be the key of the entry to be removed from the Global Associated String List (ASL). (See }{\f1\fs18\uldb\insrsid5405 Associated String Lists}{\v\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 !ALink(Associated String Lists)}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 ).
\par 
\par }{\f1\fs18\cf6\insrsid5405 Remove Level ASL}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 
\par The parameter is taken to be the key of the entry to be removed from the levels Associated String List (ASL). (See }{\f1\fs18\uldb\insrsid5405 Associated String Lists}{\v\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 !ALink(Associated String Lists)}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 ).
\par 
\par }{\f1\fs18\cf6\insrsid5405 Remove Party ASL}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 
\par The parameter is taken to be the key of the entry to be removed from the party's Associated String List (ASL). (See }{\f1\fs18\uldb\insrsid5405 Associated String Lists}{\v\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 !ALink(Associated String Lists)}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 ).
\par 
\par }{\f1\fs18\cf6\insrsid5405 Set Quest Stage}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 
\par The parameter gives the name of the quest and the new stage separated by an equal sign. The absence of an equal sign or an illegal stage number will cause the action to be ignored and a log message to be written.
\par 
\par }{\f1\fs18\cf6\insrsid5405 Set Character Attribute}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 
\par The parameter prov
ides the name or number of the character, the name of the attribute, and the new value of the attribute.  The character selection comes first and is contained in parentheses.  Assume you want to assign the value 'yes' to an attribute named 'ZPrep'.  There
 are four ways of specifying the character:
\par }{\f3\fs18\insrsid5405 \'b7}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 \tab By number.  (^3)ZPrep=yes
\par }{\f3\fs18\insrsid5405 \'b7}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 \tab By name.  (Gothmog)ZPrep=yes
\par }{\f3\fs18\insrsid5405 \'b7}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 \tab Active character  (^)ZPrep=yes
\par }{\f3\fs18\insrsid5405 \'b7}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 \tab All characters    (*)ZPrep=yes
\par If no parenthesized expression preceeds the attribute name then the active character is assumed.
\par There is no way to remove an attribute belonging to a character.  The best that you can do is to set the attribute to the empty string:
\par }{\f3\fs18\insrsid5405 \'b7}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 \tab (Gothmog)ZPrep=
\par 
\par }{\f1\fs18\cf6\insrsid5405 GPDL Function}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 
\par This is really adding insult to injury for those of you who think that things 
are already too complicated.  But here it is and it is another powerful tool.  In a nutshell....You write a GPDL function that accomplishes the action you need.  The function has the form:
\par }{\f5\fs18\insrsid5405 $PUBLIC FUNC action () \{ .......\} action;}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 
\par 
\par But you only have to write the '.......' part; the rest will be provided free of charge by the Logic Block Editor. Wow!  Now you can do anything.
\par 
\par The ampersand substitution does not work in the parameter field of this action block.  However, the values of
 all the previously computed blocks are available to the GPDL function via by using the function $LOGIC_BLOCK_VALUE(ID).  But note that if you want to reference the values of the blocks in the current event, then you must set the 'Record Values at Runtime
' control; else you will get values from some previous LOGIC_BLOCK event (in fact, this could be very useful!).
\par 
