\par }{\b\f1\fs18\cf17\insrsid5405 Editing Spells}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 
\par To edit a spell, use the menu option Database->Spells. Select a spell in the list and press the 'Edit' button. You will then see a dialog such as the one below.
\par 
\par \{bmc images\\SpellEdit.bmp\} 
\par 
\par There are several options that affect how a spell will operate. For a spell to hav
e an effect upon characters, you must add affected attributes to the attribute list. For instance, to create a healing spell called 'Cure Light Wounds' you would add to the list an attribute that modifies a character's hitpoints. The attribute system will
 be explained in more detail later.
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs18\cf6\insrsid5405 Warning!}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 
\par There are just too many possibilities and combinations for exha
ustive testing to be performed, so some things haven't been tested yet. Since spells can modify game variables there is an inherent danger of causing the program to crash. Expect problems and keep backups of your design files, and I do mean *frequent* bac
kups. The spell system should prove to be more stable in subsequent releases.
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Name:}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  The name of the spell, up to 50 characters. Every spell name must be unique. You can decorate names so that they are unique. For example, if you want Clerics and MagicUsers
 to have spells called 'Detect Magic', you can call them 'Detect Magic|cleric' and 'Detect Magic|mu'. Remember that any characters appended using '|' as in '|cleric' will only be visible in the editor, not while playing the design.
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Class:}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  Either Cleric or Magic User. This is the school of magic that the spell belongs to. Only one can be chosen.
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Can be cast by:}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  Select the character classes that will be allowed to cast this spell. This allows you to create clerical spells that can only be cast by Rangers an
d Druids (for instance). Only Magic Users can cast spells that belong to the Magic User school, so this option is disabled for Magic User spells. 
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Level:}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  The spell level. Spell progression for characters follows the ADnD 2E rules.
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Casting Time:}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 
 Specifies the time between when a caster starts casting and when the spell actually takes effect. Enter a numeric value and then choose the unit of time. You can select from four options. If not in combat, a spell will always be cast immediately. If a ca
ster is attacked in combat during this time the spell will be aborted.
\par 
\par Immediate - There is no delay before spell is cast
\par Initiative - Number of combat initiative turns
\par Rounds - Number of combat rounds
\par Turns - Number of combat turns
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 SaveVs:}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  For spells tha
t give the target a chance to make a saving throw to avoid some or all of a spell's effects. There are five possible tables to choose from. The saving throw table values come from ADnD 2E rules.
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Save Result:}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  Choose what will happen if a spell target makes a successful saving throw. There are four options. Spells that are cast upon party members by party members will not use saving throws.
\par 
\par No Save - No saving throw is allowed by the target
\par Save Negates - A successful save will avoid all spell affects
\par Save for Half - A successful save will give target only half
\par Use Player THACO - Roll 1D20 against target's THACO for saving throw.
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Duration:}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  A value which specifies how long the spell will last. This field is used in combination with the Duration Rate field. Duration is a }{\f1\fs18\uldb\insrsid5405 DICEPLUS}{\v\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 
!KLink(DicePlus)}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  field.
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Duration Rate:}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  This lets you choose the rate of time used for the duration value above.
\par 
\par In rounds - Duration indicates number of rounds
\par By damage taken - Duration indicates total damage taken in hitpoints
\par In hours - Duration is number of hours
\par In days - Duration is number of days
\par Instantaneous - means permanent, the spell effects don't expire
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Cast Price:}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  How much the party is charged for this spell if it is offered by a Temple event.
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Targeting Type:}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  What sort of method is used to select spell targets.
\par 
\par Self - can only be cast on yourself
\par 
\par Selected by count - specify a total number of targets
\par 
\par Whole party - automatically affects entire party
\par 
\par Touched targets - specify a total number of targets that are within 1 tile distance
\par 
\par Area: Circle - choose map location, the location will be the center of the circle of the configured size. All targets in the circle will be selected.
\par 
\par Selected by hit dice - choose targets until hit dice total is reached
\par 
\par Area: Line, Pick Start - choose map location, a line will be extended from this starting location. The direction of the line is determined by the relative
 orientation between caster and map location. If you select a location that is south east of the caster, then the line will extend in the south east direction.
\par 
\par Area: Line, Pick End - choose map location, all targets in a line that extends from caster to the map location will be selected.
\par 
\par Area: Square - choose map location, the location will be the center of the square of the configured size. All targets in the square will be selected.
\par 
\par Area: Cone - choose map location, the location will be the beginning of a cone (really just a triangle). The direction of the cone is determined by the relative orientation between caster and map location. If you select a location 
that is south east of the caster, then the cone will extend in the south east direction.
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Num Targets (or Self):}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  How many spell targets can be chosen. Not used if Targeting Type is Self or Whole Party. Num Targets is a }{\f1\fs18\uldb\insrsid5405 DICEPLUS}{\v\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 !KLink(DicePlus)}
{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  field.
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Target Range (or Self):}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  Valid only for three Targeting Types. Target Range is a }{\f1\fs18\uldb\insrsid5405 DICEPLUS}{\v\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 !KLink(DicePlus)}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  field.
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Sound:}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  Choose the sounds played when the spell reaches each stage (casting, in route to target, etc).
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Casting Sprite:}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  Choose the animation displayed as the spell is cast.
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 In-Route Sprite:}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  Choose the animation displayed as the spell travels from caster to target.
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Coverage Sprite:}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  Choose the image that is briefly displayed over the target or target area after the spell reaches the target. Example: t
he fireball flames that cover the target area. If the spell uses 'Area: Cone' targeting, then the coverage sprite should use the 'Directional' animation style and have eight images, one for each compass direction. The image that matches the cone orientati
on will be used. If using any other targeting type, the coverage sprite should use the 'Sequenced' animation style.
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Hit Sprite:}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  Choose the image that is briefly displayed on each target if the spell successfully affects the target.
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Linger Sprite:}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  The image that remains displayed on the map while the spell is in affect. Example: think of the stinking clouds that linger on the map until the spell expires.
\par 
\par It is used to display an animation on the combat map that covers the portion affected
\par by a lingering sp
ell, until the spell expires. Combatants who walk into the spell area are affected by the spell as if the spell was cast directly on them. The animation work in the same manner that I perceived the UA linger animation to work. That is, the spell area is c
o
vered by multiple instances of a 1x1 tile animation. The spell area being the portion of the combat map squares which are affected by the spell. The spell area has different, configurable, shapes - cone, square/rect, circle. If the spell area is a 2x2 squ
are, then there will be four instances of the same animation inside it running in sync. Each animation is the usual multi-frame strip of pics, with
\par configurable time delay between frames.
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 General Sprite Info:}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  Except when using the 'Area: Cone' targeting ty
pe, your sprites should use the 'Sequenced' animation style. Each sequenced image should be a multiple of 48 pixels in width and height. The animation sequence follows left to right. You can set the delay time between each image, and whether it loops, how
 many times to loop, and so on. 
\par 
\par The Cone animations use the Directional animation style: eight frames, one frame for each compass direction in the order of North, East, South, West, NorthWest, NorthEast, SouthWest, SouthEast.
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Special Abilities:}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  This will allow you to select from a list of special abilities that will be given to the spell target for the duration of the spell.
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Spell Attributes:}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  This allows you to add custom tags to the spell that can be queried by other spell scripts. For instanc
e, I create a spell called Protection From Fire and give it a spell attribute of 'ProtectsFromFire=1'. Then I create a second spell called Fireball, and give it a Spell Attribute of 'FireBasedSpell=1'. Assuming I have a character who has the Protection Fr
om Fire spell cast on it, I can choose to completely disable the Fireball spell when cast on this character by using an activation script for the Fireball spell such as:
\par 
\par $IF ($IS_AFFECTED_BY_SPELL_ATTR($Target(), "ProtectsFromFire"))
\par \{
\par   $RETURN false;
\par \}
\par $ELSE
\par \{
\par   $RETURN true;
\par \};
\par 
\par which would disable the Fireball spell for any spell that has the ProtectsFromFire attribute. I could also disable the spell only for the Protects From Fire spell by using this script,
\par 
\par $IF ($IS_AFFECTED_BY_SPELL($Target(), "Protection From Fire"))
\par \{
\par   $RETURN false;
\par \}
\par $ELSE
\par \{
\par   $RETURN true;
\par \};
\par 
\par which is using the spell name rather than a spell attribute. The spell names are unique, while the spell attributes can be shared by many spells.
\par 
\par To continue this example, suppose I wanted to just set the hit point damage to half instead of voiding the entire spell effect. The 'Change By' value is been calcuated based upon the DicePlus expression, and let's say it turns out to be the value -10. The
 
affected character attribute is probably $CHAR_HITPOINTS, and so in the absence of any scripts the Fireball spell will add -10 to the spell target's current hitpoints (remove 10 hitpoints). I could add a script like this to drop the damage to -5 if the sp
ell target is currently protected by a Protection From Fire spell,
\par 
\par $IF ($IS_AFFECTED_BY_SPELL_ATTR($Target(), "ProtectsFromFire"))
\par \{
\par   $RETURN ( $DIV( $TIMES($CURR_CHANGE_BY_VAL(),"-1"), 2) );
\par \};
\par 
\par This script goes into the Modification Script box. It basic
ally checks to see if the spell target is currently under the influence of a spell which has the 'ProtectsFromFire' spell attribute. If so, it queries the current Change By value which is -10, and divides it by two using the $DIV function. Since the resul
t
 of a modification script is always added to the current Change By value, an equation such as -10 + 5 = -5 is needed to reduce the damage by half. This is why the above script multiplies the current Change By value by -1 (using $TIMES) before dividing by 
2. If the Change By value is -10, we end up with -10 + 5 = -5, and if the Change By value is 10 we get 10 + -5 = 5.
\par 
\par To get even fancier, I could divide by 2 only if the spell target makes a saving throw versus spells with,
\par 
\par $IF ($IS_AFFECTED_BY_SPELL_ATTR($Target(), "ProtectsFromFire"))
\par \{
\par   $IF ($SaveVsSpell($Target())
\par   \{
\par     $RETURN ( $DIV( $TIMES($CURR_CHANGE_BY_VAL(),"-1"), 2) );
\par   \};
\par \};
\par 
\par Remember that the spell itself has a saving throw setting which can further reduce the Change By value applied to the spell target. 
\par 
\par The modification scripts will always return zero in the absence of an explicit $RETURN value, which will not modify the Change By value at all.
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Begin/End Scripts:}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  You can add a 'begin' script, which is a GPDL script which is invoked for 
each spell target as the spell is activated. You can also add an 'end' script, which is invoked when the spell expires. For permanent spells, only the 'begin' script will be executed.
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Combat Only:}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  If checked, this spell can only be cast during combat.
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Cumulative:}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 
 If checked, you can cast the same spell multiple times on a target and whatever affects it has will be cumulative. In not checked, the spell will not further affect a target which is already affected by this spell. Each affected character attribu
te can also be individually selected as being cumulative.
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Friendly Fire Ok:}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  If checked, this spell can be cast upon members of the party.
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Players can memorize:}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  If checked, this spell can be memorized and cast by players. If not checked, the players will never get the option to memorize this spell. This has no affect on monsters/NPCs in combat.

\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Allow scribing at level change:}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  Not available for Cleric spells, sin
ce Clerics have all spells available to them (within class limits). Magic Users must choose spells to add to their spell book. At each new level attained by the Magic User, a list of spells will be presented that they can choose from. If you want this spe
l
l to be automatically given to the Magic User, then check this box. The Magic User will still be given the option to choose additional spells to add to their spell book, and can choose until their spell limit is reached. You cannot automatically give more
 spells to the Magic User than are allowed by class/skill limits. If you automatically give enough spells to the Magic User so that the class/skill limits are reached, then the additional spells will be displayed but cannot be chosen.
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Lingers on map:}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  If checked, this spell lingers on the map, creating a visible area which can affect combatants if they walk into the spell area.
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Affects target once:}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  If checked, each combatant that walks into a linger spell area can be affected only once by the spell. If not 
checked, the combatant can be affected once per combat round while remaining in the linger area.
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Spell's duration on target:}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  A value which specifies how long the spell effects which are applied to the spell target will last. This field is always in terms of combat rounds, and it is a }{
\f1\fs18\uldb\insrsid5405 DICEPLUS}{\v\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 !KLink(DicePlus)}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  field.
\par 
\par Example: Suppose Hexbo casts a Stinking Cloud spell on the combat map, and it creates a 2x2 square area of effect (the linger area). Molson the Dark walks into the linger area and fails the sav
ing throw. Molson will feel the effects of this spell for the duration specifed by the field 'Spell's duration on target'. The Stinking Cloud spell has a separate duration specified elsewhere. The Stinking Cloud spell might expire before Molson stops feel
ing the spell's effects, or vice versa.
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Attributes:}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  This list displays all character }{\f1\fs18\uldb\insrsid5405 attributes}{\v\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 !KLink(Attribute Introduction)}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 
 that can be affected by the spell. Four columns are shown:
\par 
\par Affected - shows the actual attribute affected, such as '$CHAR_THACO'
\par Change by - shows the delta value applied to the attribute
\par Cumulative - Yes/No
\par Activation - shows the activation script used, if any.
\par 
\par You can choose to 'Add', 'Delete', or 'Edit' each attribute in the list by highlighting one with the mouse and pushing the appropriate button. Attributes in the list will be modified for the duration of the spell.
\par 
\par Each attribute in the list will be modified in the order listed. When writing scripts keep in mind that character values being queried may return values that have
 been modified by an attribute modification that came earlier in the list. In other words, the ordering of the attribute modifications might be an issue if subsequent scripts rely on character values having their unmodified values.
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 General Information:}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 
\par 
\par A spell does not always need to modify character attributes. For instance, a Magic User spell called 'Knock' is available by default and it does not modify anything. However, it can be specified by the wall slot editor as the spell which unlocks doors. Si
mply by having it memorized, a character will be given the option to cast Knock when faced with a locked door requiring this spell.
\par 
\par Spells can be created that will never be available for use by the party. For instance, a spell called 'MonsterPoison' is available by default and it is used for special attacks by monsters that can poison characters.
\par 
\par Spells can give or take items to/from characters. For instance, the spell called 'Spiritual Hammer' invokes a script that grants an item called 'Spiritual Hammer'
 to the spell target. This item exists in the item database by default. For the duration of the spell, the spell target can 'Ready' this weapon and use it in combat. When the spell expires, the item is removed from the character.
\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\sb50\sa50\keepn\nowidctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 \page }{\cs18\super\insrsid5405\charrsid5405 ${\footnote\ftnalt \pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 
