\par Now some general notes on converting FRUA art to something usable with DC:
\par 
\par I have been using Paint Shop Pro 6 to do this, so your results may vary. 
\par 
\par After conversions are completed, place the correct transparent color at 0,0 if needed (see below for transparency). I would recommend using caution when
\par anti-aliasing images that use transparency since this can alter the transparent pixels slightly and they will be mistakenly drawn to the screen.
\par 
\par To convert:
\par 
\par Icons:
\par 
\par Resize to 640x286 maintaining aspect ratio, move one of the tiles so
\par that it directly abuts it's neighbor, crop image down to just icon data. Result should be a multiple of 48 in both directions.
\par 
\par Big Pics,Small Pics,Backdrops:
\par 
\par Resize to 640x480 *without* maintaining aspect ratio, crop down to include only image data.
\par 
\par Combat walls:
\par 
\par Resize to 640x400 maintaining aspect ratio. The file can be made smaller by
\par cropping the image down so that the empty black space is removed.
\par 
\par Doors, overlays, walls:
\par 
\par Resize to 640x480 *without* maintaining aspect ratio. The walls can be
\par cropped down to reduce file size. The doors/overlays take some extra work, but the goal is to make the image data for each door/overlay align with coordinates used by the corresponding wall images:
\par 
\par }{\f3\fs18\insrsid5405 \'b7}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 \tab add 130 pixels to left side of image, making it 770 pixels wide
\par }{\f3\fs18\insrsid5405 \'b7}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 \tab move last image that is in upper right corner to second row, left side. Should be 0,120 for the upper left pixel.
\par }{\f3\fs18\insrsid5405 \'b7}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 \tab at this point the wall and door/overlay images should align for x
 coordinates, but the y coords (vertical) need to be tweaked for each door/overlay. Simply determine the bottom y coord for each wall image, and move the corresponding door/overlay up or down so that it's bottom y coord matches.
\par }{\f3\fs18\insrsid5405 \'b7}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 \tab the largest door/overlay image may need to be moved slightly to the right to make it be drawn in the center of the largest wall section.
\par }{\f3\fs18\insrsid5405 \'b7}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 \tab since walls/doors/overlays use transparency, either the bounding boxes for the doors/overlays need to enlarged to match the wall boxes, or, th
e quickest procedure is to fill the black areas of the image with the transparent green color, then color the pink boxes in the green color also.
\par 
\par For all artwork, if an image will be drawn using transparency, the transparent color is always determined from the color of the image pixel at 0,0 (upper left). Whatever that color is, it will not be transferred >from the source.
\par 
\par At the moment, the following pic types use transparency:
\par 
\par Sprites
\par Walls
\par Doors
\par Overlays
\par Icons
\par Fonts (except highlight font)
\par 
\par and the following pics do not use it:
\par 
\par title
\par combat walls, indoor and outdoor
\par backdrops
\par maps
\par big pics
\par small pics (even when animated, although this might become user selectable at some point)
\par combat cursor
\par combat death animation
\par frame art
\par area view art
\par 
