\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\b\f1\fs18\cf17\insrsid5405 Introduction}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 
\par 
\par Have you ever thought after finishing a commercial Role Playing Game "I could have thought of a better 
ending" or  "I would have told this story better"? Have you ever had an idea and thought "This would make a great game, it is a pity that I am not able to program it"? With UAForever/Dungeon Craft you have the best tool to create your own game without pro
gramming abilities.
\par 
\par Originally based on the commercial DOS-game-designer }{\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Unlimited Adventures}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  from SSI }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 UAForever/Dungeon Craft}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 
 was improved and extended counting in the wishes of designers. So }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Dungeon Craft (DC)}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  is really almost unlimited in the possibilities  to create designs.
\par 
\par All you need is a good painting program or picture editor, the UAFWinEd.exe from }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 UAForever/Dungeon Craft}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 , and lots of creativity. With these tools you have the possibility to create whole new worlds.
\par 
\par But before you can start creating your own adventures you will need to learn how to use this tool. This chapter describes the major steps required in order to design your own role playing adventure. It assumes that you are familiar with Windows and Gold B
ox games or at least using menus and a mouse.
