\par }{\b\f1\fs18\cf17\insrsid5405 Fixing Mistakes}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 
\par 
\par Since making mistakes and changing your mind are normal parts of any design process, DC makes it easy to undo changes. 
\par 
\par In every }{\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Mode}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  that works on the initial work space you can reverse many simple actions by just pressing the right mouse button. Pressing this button takes back the item you click on. 
\par 
\par The }{\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Event Mode}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 
 works a bit different since a new dialog is opened if you click on a square in the map grid. You can delete and revert your actions right in this dialog, you can even delete complete event chains.
\par 
\par If you save changes and later wish you hadn't, you might be able to recover the earlier version. It is always a good idea to back up your work, by keeping }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 backups}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 
 of the needed files when you have finished an editing session. That way, if you wish to discard all changes that you just saved, you can replace the adventure design in your UAF-directory with the backup copy. 
