\par 
\par The brown floor and the green sky look fine with the walls but maybe you should think about roofs for some of your chambers. You can change floor and ceiling images when the editor is in }{\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Backdrop Mode}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 
, so press the }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 B-button}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  in the toolbar now.
\par  
\par Notice that the walls in the area map appear simpler, since obstruction levels are only shown in wall mode. Also notice that all black squares in the map are filled with a small dark blue on every side.
\par 
\par To get an overview over the currently available backdrops press the }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Select Backdrop}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 -button on the left side. A dialog window similar to the }{\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Wall Slot Dialog}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 
 appears. }{\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Backdrop 3}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  looks like a backdrop with a wooden roof. So that is the one to choose now.
\par 
\par If you double click on the slot or press the }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Load Slot}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 
 button another window opens. This is the window where you can load other customized backdrops. Notice that there is also an alternate slot available. This is for showing a different backdrop by night. Close the }{\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Background}{
\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  window and the }{\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Backdrop Selection}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  without changing anything. It is time to place the backdrop on the map.
\par 
\par Move the party cursor to a room on the map you have drawn. The room should be at least 2 x 2 squares big. As you already know, t
he movement works with the arrow keys but there is a shortcut to set the party into the square you wish: press the CRTL-button on your keyboard and left-click with the mouse into the square you want the party to be.
\par 
\par Now you can place }{\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Backdrop 3}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  in the squ
are where the small white arrow is by just left-clicking there with the mouse or by clicking on the button "Place Backdrop". Notice that the buttons "Left" and "Right" are dimmed now. If you did this correctly, the color-code for backdrop slot 3 - dark gr
e
en - will now be on all four sides of the grid square you are in and the 3D-view should show the background with the wooden ceiling now. Keep on filling the room with the new backdrop now. If you went too far and drew in a square you didn't intend to fill
 with this new backdrop, you can easily restore }{\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Backdrop 2}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  by clicking on the button 2 in the }{\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Legend}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  and replace it again. 
\par 
\par Differently from }{\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Unlimited Adventures}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  in }{\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 DC}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  it is possible to have different backdrops on each side of a square, having for example 
a moon shown in the west and a sun shown in the east. For this you have to de-select "Place Backdrop on all Sides" in the }{\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Mode}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 
-menu. Now only the backdrop in front of the party is replaced or the backdrop on the side you clicked on.
\par 
\par It is also possible to fill the whole map or parts of it with the currently chosen backdrop. You can do this by clicking in the Level menu on }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Fill All Map - Backdrop - All Facings}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 .
\par 
\par Just play a little around with the different backdrops now. You will find that many interesting effects can be created with them.
\par 
\par If you are content with what you have done, it is time to save again.
