\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Backdrop}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  color code has changed. Now there are only black squares in each grid square of the  level. In the Legend you can see that black is the color code for }{\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Zone 1}{
\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 . Since the room you just changed is different from the rest of your dungeon, you might wish to make it a different zone as well. Chose }{\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Zone 2}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  by clicking on the }{
\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 2}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  in the }{\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Legend}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  and replace the black squares in your room with the blue ones.
\par 
\par Now that was easy, wasn't it? But right now, there is no difference between }{\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Zone 1}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  and }{\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Zone 2}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 , since they are all equal by default. How about making }{
\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Zone 2}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  different from }{\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Zone 1}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 ?
\par 
\par It is easy to achieve this. Just click on the }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Select Zone button}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 . The }{\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Zone Data Window}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 
 appears. Here you can change the name of the zone and some of the global settings, like for example the Camp Art. Since this zone is indoo
rs the art should maybe be changed for indoor resting. Unfortunately you don't have another camp picture yet. Then maybe you don't want the party to rest in this zone. This can be triggered by selecting the }{\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Cant Rest in this Zone}
{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 -option.
\par  
\par If you are content with your changes, press OK and return to the main editor.
\par 
\par Time to save again, don't you think?
