\par }{\b\f1\fs18\cf17\insrsid5405 Designing an Event}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 
\par 
\par This chapter will lead you through the steps of placing and editing a text event in one of the corridors or rooms you constructed in the previous chapter. You will fill in the answers in the }{\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Text Statement}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 
. Answering these questions will introduce you to several of the types of controls used in }{\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 DC}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 .
\par 
\par First you have to press the }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 E-button}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  in the toolbar. You are now in }{\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Event Mode}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 .
\par 
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs18\cf17\insrsid5405 Creating a New Event}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 
\par 
\par Set the party cursor in the square on the map where you want the event to happen. For example you could want to give the party information about the room with the roof you created. 
\par 
\par Notice that in }{\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Event Mode}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  almost every other option is dimmed. There is only one option active, the }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Place Event}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  button. Make sure
 that you are in the right position just behind the door inside your room and press this button or left-click with your mouse into the appropriate square on the map.
\par 
\par The }{\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Event Viewer Dialog}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  appears. First you will have to select the type of event you want to create. You can select it by opening the }{\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Event Type}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 
 list. Just click into the dialog field and select the event type }{\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Text Statement}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 . 
\par Now click on the }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Add}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 -button under the event tree. Another dialog appears with the specific questionnaire for the text 
event. Now you can decide on what the player sees, what the player hears and what he will read. Feel free to play around with the settings a bit. 
\par 
\par To add a picture, click on the button currently labled }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Nothing}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  in the line }{\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Player Sees}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 . The }{\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Picture selection}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 
 will appear. This dialog will pop up whenever you want to select a picture for any event. Select }{\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Small Picture}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  and click on the }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Load/View}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 
-button. Another dialog will appear where you can click on the }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Load}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 -button.  Since you never loaded a picture before you have to click yourself through your sub folders. Select the }{\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 
Tutorial.dsn}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  sub folder in your UAF-folder. There you should search for a picture beginning with "prt_...". These are the portraits. Choose one of the four default portraits that are supplied with }{\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 DC}{
\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 . 
\par 
\par Repeat this procedure for choosing one of the default sounds that will be heard while the event is occurring.
\par 
\par Unlike }{\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Unlimited Adventures}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  in }{\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 DC}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  there is only one textbox per }{\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Text Statement}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 
 available. As stated in the dialog you can highlight text by toggling "/h". Just write the text }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 "This is a /h special /h room"}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 . 
\par 
\par If you are content with all the changes leave the Dialog with "OK" and save those changes by clicking on the }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Save}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 -disk in the toolbar.
