\par }{\b\f1\fs18\cf17\insrsid5405 Step Events}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 
\par 
\par Step Events are events assigned to one or more }{\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Zones}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 . Up to 8 step events per level are possible, but you can create long chains with them, triggering one after the other (by setting each on }{
\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Once Only}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 ) or by triggering it on }{\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Random Chance}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 . A step event may be of any type. 
\par 
\par Enter the }{\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Event Mode}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  and click on your already existing event to get the }{\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Event Viewer}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 . Expand the }{\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Event Tree}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 
 by clicking on the }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 +}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 -symbol in front of }{\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Step Events}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 . A list with the 8 possible events opens, currently all set to }{\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 "No Event"}{
\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 . Select the first }{\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Step Event}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  and select }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Combat}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  and press }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Add}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 . 
\par 
\par Write into the "Player reads" field: }{\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 "You are under attack."}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  Select the Monster "Giant Rat" and let 2 of them start out nearby. Now you have to define where this }{\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 step event}{
\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  will happen. Since you only have two defined zones, it should only happen in one of these zones, for example }{\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Zone 1}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 .
\par 
\par Click on the }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Step Events}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 -button below the event tree and define that this event should happen every }{\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 10 steps}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  in }{\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Zone 1}{
\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 .
\par 
\par The first time the party takes a step in }{\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Zone 1}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  the step counter will be set to zero. Each
 step the party takes while inside this zone will add one to this counter. Counting will stop as soon as the party moves out of the }{\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Zone}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 
 into a map square with a different number. If the party re-enters any map square belonging to }{\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Zone 1}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 , counting will sta
rt up again where it left off. As soon as the counter for this step event reaches the number 10, the counter is reset to zero and the designated event occurs.
\par 
\par Now save all and test your changes, if you want.
\par 
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs18\cf17\insrsid5405 Rest Events}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 
\par 
\par }{\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Rest Events}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  work exactly like }{\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Step Events}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 . They are triggered each time the party tries to rest in the selected }{\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Zone}{
\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 . The only difference is that }{\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Rest Events}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  only happen in the specified zone they were created for. If you want a for example a }{\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Text Statement}{
\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  happen while resting in }{\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Zone 1}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  as well as in }{\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Zone 4}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 
 you have to create that Text Statement twice as Rest Event for Zone 1 and as Rest Event for Zone 4.
\par 
\par }{\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Rest events}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  interrupt the resting of the party, making it sometimes impossible to learn their magic spells or to heal their wounds in the particular zone. Usually they are simple }{\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 
Text Statements}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 , stating the party should go to an inn to take their rest or a }{\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Combat}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  event, simulating roaming monsters who found the sleeping party members. If they are triggered by 
}{\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Random Chance}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  the party can be lucky and have an undisturbed night. 
