\par In }{\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Unlimited Adventures}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  there were three different events to carry the party to a different region of the map or even to another level. You can still find the events }{\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Stairs}{
\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  and }{\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Teleporter}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  in the event list but in }{\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 DC}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  they are all linked with the }{\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Transfer Module}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 
. So there is no difference which kind of }{\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Transfer}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  you choose.
\par 
\par Place a new event into one corner of your special room (for example the north-east corner). Select }{\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Transfer Module}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  in the event list and add the new event.
\par 
\par In the new }{\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Transfer Data}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  dialog you can choose if the party will be asked before transporting. Write a short question, like "Do you want to use the Teleporter?". Click on the }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 
Teleport}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  button to define the destination. In this event this will be }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Entry Point 2}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  in }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Level 1}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 
. De-select the option "Execute event at destination" and press }{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 OK}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 . You can choose to write a small note the party will read after the transfer if you want.
\par 
\par Now the party will be transported to the new room whenever they enter the north-east corner of the special room and answer "yes".
\par 
\par Since the new room in our example doesn't have any doors or other exits, it would be better to give the party the opportunity to leave it via Teleporter again.
\par 
\par Set up a new event at the place where }{\i\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 Entry Point 2}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  was set to teleport the party back to where they came from. Remember to de-select "Execute event at destination" to not let them loop in and out. Use the }
{\b\f1\fs18\insrsid5405 X,Y coordinates}{\f1\fs18\insrsid5405  to teleport them back.
\par 
\par Save your work and test it, if you like.
